<h2>Legal and Law Firms &#123;#legal&#125;</h2>
<p>Legal directories are among the most established niche citation sources online. Courts, bar associations, and prospective clients all use these platforms to verify attorney credentials. A complete profile on the right <a href="/blog/law-firm-seo-guide/">law firm SEO</a> directories can generate direct client inquiries.</p>
<p><strong>1. Avvo</strong> (<a href="https://www.avvo.com">avvo.com</a>). The largest attorney directory in the U.S. with over 97% of lawyers listed. Includes peer endorsements, client reviews, and an Avvo Rating score. Every practicing attorney should claim this profile immediately.</p>
<p><strong>2. FindLaw</strong> (<a href="https://www.findlaw.com">findlaw.com</a>). Thomson Reuters-owned legal directory with high domain authority. Offers free basic listings and paid enhanced profiles. Best for firms wanting visibility on one of the most-searched legal platforms.</p>
<p><strong>3. Justia</strong> (<a href="https://www.justia.com">justia.com</a>). Free lawyer directory with detailed practice area pages. Allows case results, publications, and speaking engagements. Strong organic traffic from people searching for specific legal issues.</p>
<p><strong>4. Lawyers.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.lawyers.com">lawyers.com</a>). Martindale-Hubbell powered directory connecting clients with rated attorneys. Peer review ratings carry significant weight. Ideal for established firms with strong reputations.</p>
<p><strong>5. Martindale-Hubbell</strong> (<a href="https://www.martindale.com">martindale.com</a>). The oldest legal directory in the U.S., operating since 1868. AV Preeminent ratings are recognized across the legal profession. Essential for credibility with other attorneys and corporate clients.</p>
<p><strong>6. Super Lawyers</strong> (<a href="https://www.superlawyers.com">superlawyers.com</a>). Rating service that selects top attorneys through peer nominations and research. Only 5% of attorneys earn this designation. Excellent for differentiating your firm from competitors.</p>
<p><strong>7. Nolo</strong> (<a href="https://www.nolo.com">nolo.com</a>). Legal information site with an attorney directory organized by practice area and location. Strong organic traffic from people with specific legal questions. Good for consumer-facing practices.</p>
<p><strong>8. LawInfo</strong> (<a href="https://www.lawinfo.com">lawinfo.com</a>). Attorney directory with practice area guides and legal resources. Includes free and paid listing options. Serves family law, personal injury, and criminal defense practices well.</p>
<p><strong>9. HG.org</strong> (<a href="https://www.hg.org">hg.org</a>). Global legal directory with listings in 160+ countries. Free basic listings available. Best for international law firms or practices serving cross-border clients.</p>
<p><strong>10. LegalMatch</strong> (<a href="https://www.legalmatch.com">legalmatch.com</a>). Lead-generation platform matching clients with attorneys by case type. Attorneys receive direct case inquiries. Works best for solo practitioners and small firms.</p>
<p><strong>11. Lawyer Legion</strong> (<a href="https://www.lawyerlegion.com">lawyerlegion.com</a>). Free attorney directory with practice area and location filters. Includes bar admission verification. A solid supplementary listing for any practicing lawyer.</p>
<p><strong>12. Attorney Pages</strong> (<a href="https://www.attorneypages.com">attorneypages.com</a>). Specialized directory focused on connecting clients with attorneys by specialty. Simple profiles with contact information and practice areas. Good for broadening your citation footprint.</p>
<p><strong>13. American Bar Association</strong> (<a href="https://www.americanbar.org">americanbar.org</a>). The national bar association directory. Membership listings confirm active bar status. Required for credibility in the legal profession.</p>
<p><strong>14. NOLO Lawyer Directory</strong> (<a href="https://lawyers.nolo.com">lawyers.nolo.com</a>). Distinct from the main Nolo site, this directory features detailed attorney profiles with Q&amp;A content. Great for attorneys who want to demonstrate subject matter expertise through written answers.</p>
<h2>Healthcare and Medical &#123;#healthcare&#125;</h2>
<p>Healthcare directories directly influence patient acquisition. <a href="/blog/healthcare-seo-guide/">Healthcare SEO</a> depends on consistent, accurate listings across these platforms. Patients trust verified credentials, specialty information, and peer reviews before booking appointments.</p>
<p><strong>15. Zocdoc</strong> (<a href="https://www.zocdoc.com">zocdoc.com</a>). Online appointment booking platform used by millions of patients monthly. Verified insurance acceptance and real-time availability. Essential for any practice that wants new patient volume.</p>
<p><strong>16. Healthgrades</strong> (<a href="https://www.healthgrades.com">healthgrades.com</a>). Largest physician directory in the U.S. with 3+ billion searches annually. Patient satisfaction scores and quality metrics displayed prominently. Every doctor and hospital should maintain an updated profile.</p>
<p><strong>17. Vitals</strong> (<a href="https://www.vitals.com">vitals.com</a>). Doctor reviews and ratings platform with detailed provider profiles. Includes patient experience indicators and wait time data. Useful for practices focused on transparency.</p>
<p><strong>18. WebMD Physician Directory</strong> (<a href="https://doctor.webmd.com">doctor.webmd.com</a>). Directory embedded within the most-visited health information website. Reaches patients actively researching conditions and treatments. High trust signal for search engines.</p>
<p><strong>19. Doximity</strong> (<a href="https://www.doximity.com">doximity.com</a>). Professional medical network with over 80% of U.S. physicians registered. Enables secure communication and referral connections. Important for building professional referral networks.</p>
<p><strong>20. CareDash</strong> (<a href="https://www.caredash.com">caredash.com</a>). Free physician directory with transparent review policies. Does not allow doctors to remove negative reviews. Builds trust through authentic patient feedback.</p>
<p><strong>21. RateMDs</strong> (<a href="https://www.ratemds.com">ratemds.com</a>). Doctor rating and review site active since 2004. Covers physicians across the U.S. and Canada. Valuable for practices in competitive metro markets.</p>
<p><strong>22. Sharecare</strong> (<a href="https://www.sharecare.com">sharecare.com</a>). Health engagement platform founded by Dr. Oz and Jeff Arnold. Includes physician search with detailed credentials. Good for reaching health-conscious consumers.</p>
<p><strong>23. Wellness.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.wellness.com">wellness.com</a>). Directory focused on holistic and integrative health providers. Covers acupuncturists, naturopaths, and wellness coaches. Best for alternative medicine practitioners.</p>
<p><strong>24. Doctor.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.doctor.com">doctor.com</a>). Patient engagement platform with directory listings and reputation management. Syndicated profiles reach multiple consumer sites. Useful for multi-location practices.</p>
<p><strong>25. Caredash</strong> (<a href="https://www.caredash.com">caredash.com</a>). Transparent review platform that does not let providers suppress feedback. Free profiles with verified information. Signals authenticity to both patients and search engines.</p>
<p><strong>26. ZocDoc</strong> (<a href="https://www.zocdoc.com/practice">zocdoc.com/practice</a>). The provider-facing portal for managing your Zocdoc presence. Allows scheduling integration and insurance verification. Priority for practices accepting new patients.</p>
<p><strong>27. Castlight Health</strong> (<a href="https://www.castlighthealth.com">castlighthealth.com</a>). Healthcare navigation platform used by large employers. Connects employees with in-network providers. Important for practices serving corporate health plans.</p>
<p><strong>28. Amino</strong> (<a href="https://amino.com">amino.com</a>). Healthcare transparency platform with cost and quality data. Helps patients find doctors based on outcomes. Relevant for specialists with strong track records.</p>
<p><strong>29. HealthSoul</strong> (<a href="https://www.healthsoul.com">healthsoul.com</a>). Patient-driven review platform for physicians and specialists. Detailed provider profiles with appointment booking. A growing directory worth claiming early.</p>
<p><strong>30. Practo</strong> (<a href="https://www.practo.com">practo.com</a>). International healthcare directory with strong presence in Asia and growing U.S. footprint. Online consultation features attract digitally engaged patients. Worth listing for practices serving diverse populations.</p>
