<h2>Dental &#123;#dental&#125;</h2>
<p>Dentists operate in one of the most competitive local search markets. The right <a href="/blog/dental-seo-guide/">dental SEO</a> citations separate practices that fill chairs from those that struggle for new patients. These directories are where prospective patients compare dentists before booking.</p>
<p><strong>31. 1-800-Dentist</strong> (<a href="https://www.1800dentist.com">1800dentist.com</a>). One of the most recognized dental referral services in the U.S. Connects patients with dentists by location and insurance. Strong brand recognition drives direct patient inquiries.</p>
<p><strong>32. Dentists.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.dentists.com">dentists.com</a>). Dental-specific directory with practice profiles and patient reviews. Clean interface focused entirely on dental care. Excellent keyword-rich domain for SEO value.</p>
<p><strong>33. Opencare</strong> (<a href="https://www.opencare.com">opencare.com</a>). Patient matching platform for dental practices. Uses algorithm-based matching to connect patients with compatible dentists. Works well in major metro markets.</p>
<p><strong>34. Dental Plans</strong> (<a href="https://www.dentalplans.com">dentalplans.com</a>). Directory of dentists accepting discount dental plans. Lists over 100,000 dental providers. Useful for practices that accept discount plans as a patient acquisition channel.</p>
<p><strong>35. ADA Find a Dentist</strong> (<a href="https://www.ada.org/findadentist">ada.org/findadentist</a>). The American Dental Association official directory. Only ADA member dentists appear. Membership listing signals professional credibility to patients and Google.</p>
<p><strong>36. Dentist Directory</strong> (<a href="https://www.dentistdirectory.com">dentistdirectory.com</a>). Simple dental directory organized by state and specialty. Free basic listings available. Adds a dental-specific citation to your profile.</p>
<p><strong>37. Smile Guide</strong> (<a href="https://www.smileguide.com">smileguide.com</a>). Cosmetic dentistry directory connecting patients with cosmetic dental providers. Focused on veneers, whitening, and smile makeovers. Best for practices offering aesthetic services.</p>
<p><strong>38. Dentistry.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.dentistry.com">dentistry.com</a>). Dental information portal with a provider directory. Educational content drives organic traffic from patients researching procedures. Good supplementary citation source.</p>
<p><strong>39. Dental Departures</strong> (<a href="https://www.dentaldepartures.com">dentaldepartures.com</a>). International dental tourism directory. Includes patient reviews and price comparisons. Relevant for practices in border areas or tourist destinations.</p>
<p><strong>40. Emergency Dentists USA</strong> (<a href="https://www.emergencydentistsusa.com">emergencydentistsusa.com</a>). Directory focused on emergency dental services by city. Attracts high-intent patients with urgent needs. Important for practices offering same-day emergency appointments.</p>
<h2>Real Estate &#123;#real-estate&#125;</h2>
<p>Real estate agents depend on directory visibility more than almost any other profession. Homebuyers and sellers check multiple platforms before choosing an agent. A strong <a href="/blog/real-estate-seo-guide/">real estate SEO</a> strategy includes all of these directories.</p>
<p><strong>41. Zillow</strong> (<a href="https://www.zillow.com">zillow.com</a>). The dominant real estate marketplace in the U.S. with over 200 million monthly visitors. Agent profiles with past sales, reviews, and active listings. Non-negotiable for every real estate professional.</p>
<p><strong>42. Realtor.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.realtor.com">realtor.com</a>). Official site of the National Association of Realtors. Feeds from MLS databases and features agent directories. Second only to Zillow in consumer traffic.</p>
<p><strong>43. Redfin</strong> (<a href="https://www.redfin.com">redfin.com</a>). Technology-driven real estate brokerage with agent profiles. Features market data and home value estimates. Useful for agents in markets where Redfin operates.</p>
<p><strong>44. Homes.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.homes.com">homes.com</a>). CoStar-owned real estate portal with growing traffic. Agent profiles with listing history and contact options. Gaining market share rapidly after CoStar acquisition.</p>
<p><strong>45. Trulia</strong> (<a href="https://www.trulia.com">trulia.com</a>). Zillow Group property with neighborhood-focused search. Crime maps, school ratings, and commute data attract buyers. Agent profiles benefit from the research-heavy audience.</p>
<p><strong>46. HomeFinder</strong> (<a href="https://www.homefinder.com">homefinder.com</a>). Real estate listing and agent directory. Free agent profiles available. A supplementary citation that reinforces your real estate niche.</p>
<p><strong>47. LoopNet</strong> (<a href="https://www.loopnet.com">loopnet.com</a>). The largest commercial real estate marketplace. Essential for agents and brokers specializing in commercial properties. Over 10 million monthly visitors in the commercial space.</p>
<p><strong>48. LandWatch</strong> (<a href="https://www.landwatch.com">landwatch.com</a>). Directory for land, farms, and rural property listings. Niche but valuable for agents in rural markets. Reaches buyers specifically looking for land parcels.</p>
<p><strong>49. Movoto</strong> (<a href="https://www.movoto.com">movoto.com</a>). Real estate listing platform with agent profiles and market reports. Clean user interface attracts serious buyers. Worth listing for additional citation diversity.</p>
<p><strong>50. RealtyTrac</strong> (<a href="https://www.realtytrac.com">realtytrac.com</a>). Foreclosure and distressed property listing site. Agent profiles appear alongside property data. Valuable for agents specializing in foreclosures or investment properties.</p>
<p><strong>51. Hotpads</strong> (<a href="https://www.hotpads.com">hotpads.com</a>). Zillow Group rental-focused platform. Agent and property manager profiles. Important for agents who handle rental properties.</p>
<p><strong>52. RealEstateAgent.com</strong> (<a href="https://www.realestateagent.com">realestateagent.com</a>). Dedicated agent directory with reviews and transaction history. Focused solely on connecting consumers with agents. Strong keyword relevance in the domain name.</p>
<h2>Restaurants and Food Service &#123;#restaurants&#125;</h2>
<p>Restaurant directories drive direct revenue. Every listing is a potential reservation or takeout order. <a href="/blog/restaurant-seo-guide/">Restaurant SEO</a> requires presence on these platforms because diners check reviews and menus before deciding where to eat.</p>
<p><strong>53. TripAdvisor</strong> (<a href="https://www.tripadvisor.com">tripadvisor.com</a>). The world's largest travel and restaurant review platform with 463 million monthly visitors. Restaurant reviews influence tourist and local dining decisions equally. A top-priority listing for any food establishment.</p>
<p><strong>54. OpenTable</strong> (<a href="https://www.opentable.com">opentable.com</a>). Leading restaurant reservation platform. Directly generates seated diners through online bookings. Vital for full-service restaurants that accept reservations.</p>
<p><strong>55. Zomato</strong> (<a href="https://www.zomato.com">zomato.com</a>). Restaurant discovery and food delivery platform operating globally. Menus, photos, and reviews help diners choose. Strong presence in metro areas and college towns.</p>
<p><strong>56. Grubhub</strong> (<a href="https://www.grubhub.com">grubhub.com</a>). Food delivery marketplace serving thousands of U.S. cities. Listing here means appearing in delivery search results. Necessary for restaurants offering delivery service.</p>
<p><strong>57. DoorDash</strong> (<a href="https://www.doordash.com">doordash.com</a>). The largest food delivery platform in the U.S. by market share. A storefront page acts as a mini-website for your restaurant. Critical for restaurants with a delivery revenue stream.</p>
<p><strong>58. Uber Eats</strong> (<a href="https://www.ubereats.com">ubereats.com</a>). Food delivery arm of Uber with a massive user base. Reaches consumers who may not search on Google for restaurants. Important for capturing delivery-first customers.</p>
<p><strong>59. MenuPages</strong> (<a href="https://www.menupages.com">menupages.com</a>). Restaurant menus and reviews integrated with Grubhub. Focused on the menu browsing experience. Useful for restaurants in cities where MenuPages has strong traffic.</p>
<p><strong>60. AllMenus</strong> (<a href="https://www.allmenus.com">allmenus.com</a>). Menu aggregation site with restaurant listings. Allows customers to view full menus before visiting. Low-effort listing that adds citation diversity.</p>
<p><strong>61. EatStreet</strong> (<a href="https://www.eatstreet.com">eatstreet.com</a>). Online food ordering platform for restaurants. Smaller than Grubhub but strong in specific regional markets. Worth listing for restaurants in EatStreet cities.</p>
<p><strong>62. HappyCow</strong> (<a href="https://www.happycow.net">happycow.net</a>). Directory for vegan and vegetarian restaurants worldwide. Passionate community of plant-based diners. Essential for any restaurant with vegan or vegetarian options.</p>
<p><strong>63. The Infatuation</strong> (<a href="https://www.theinfatuation.com">theinfatuation.com</a>). Curated restaurant review platform owned by JPMorgan Chase. Trusted editorial reviews carry significant influence. Submission-based, so reach out for consideration.</p>
<p><strong>64. Zagat</strong> (<a href="https://www.zagat.com">zagat.com</a>). Iconic restaurant survey and guide now owned by The Infatuation. Historic brand recognition still carries SEO and trust value. Worth pursuing for established restaurants.</p>
