<h2>Home Services &#123;#home-services&#125;</h2>
<p>Homeowners search for service providers with urgency. A leaking pipe or broken furnace means they need someone now. <a href="/blog/home-services-seo-guide/">Home services SEO</a> depends on being listed where these high-intent searches happen.</p>
<p><strong>65. Angi</strong> (<a href="https://www.angi.com">angi.com</a>). Formerly Angie's List, this is the largest home services marketplace. Verified reviews and background-checked professionals. The most important niche directory for any home service business.</p>
<p><strong>66. HomeAdvisor</strong> (<a href="https://www.homeadvisor.com">homeadvisor.com</a>). Now merged with Angi under the same parent company. Still operates separately with its own traffic and lead system. Submit to both for maximum coverage.</p>
<p><strong>67. Thumbtack</strong> (<a href="https://www.thumbtack.com">thumbtack.com</a>). Service marketplace connecting homeowners with local professionals. Covers everything from plumbing to painting. Strong lead generation for service-based businesses.</p>
<p><strong>68. Houzz</strong> (<a href="https://www.houzz.com">houzz.com</a>). Home design and renovation platform with a professional directory. Ideal for contractors, architects, interior designers, and landscapers. Portfolio features let you showcase completed projects.</p>
<p><strong>69. Porch</strong> (<a href="https://www.porch.com">porch.com</a>). Home services marketplace with contractor profiles and project matching. Integrates with Lowe's for additional lead flow. Good for renovation and remodeling contractors.</p>
<p><strong>70. Bark</strong> (<a href="https://www.bark.com">bark.com</a>). Service marketplace operating in the U.S. and U.K. Covers home services, events, and professional services. Growing platform with less competition than Angi.</p>
<p><strong>71. Networx</strong> (<a href="https://www.networx.com">networx.com</a>). Home improvement lead generation platform. Connects homeowners with screened contractors. Delivers project-specific leads rather than general traffic.</p>
<p><strong>72. BuildZoom</strong> (<a href="https://www.buildzoom.com">buildzoom.com</a>). Contractor directory with license verification and project history. Pulls data from state licensing boards. Excellent credibility signal for licensed contractors.</p>
<p><strong>73. Directorii</strong> (<a href="https://www.directorii.com">directorii.com</a>). Curated home service contractor directory with a $20,000 guarantee. Only certified contractors are listed. Premium positioning for contractors willing to stand behind their work.</p>
<p><strong>74. House Call Pro</strong> (<a href="https://www.housecallpro.com">housecallpro.com</a>). Field service management software with a consumer-facing directory. Customers can book services directly. Useful for <a href="/blog/social-media-for-plumbers/">plumber</a>, <a href="/blog/electrician-seo-guide/">electrician</a>, and HVAC businesses.</p>
<p><strong>75. CraftJack</strong> (<a href="https://www.craftjack.com">craftjack.com</a>). Lead generation platform for home improvement professionals. Delivers real-time leads from homeowners requesting quotes. Good supplement to organic search efforts.</p>
<p><strong>76. Kukun</strong> (<a href="https://www.kukun.com">kukun.com</a>). Home renovation platform with contractor matching and ROI calculators. Attracts homeowners planning renovation projects. Relevant for remodeling contractors and kitchen/bath specialists.</p>
<p><strong>77. TaskRabbit</strong> (<a href="https://www.taskrabbit.com">taskrabbit.com</a>). On-demand home services platform owned by IKEA. Covers handyman work, furniture assembly, moving help, and cleaning. Best for handymen and general service providers.</p>
<p><strong>78. Handy</strong> (<a href="https://www.handy.com">handy.com</a>). Home cleaning and handyman booking platform. Acquired by Angi in 2018 but still operates its own marketplace. Worth listing for cleaning and handyman services.</p>
