<h2>How to Choose the Right Niche Directories &#123;#how-to-choose&#125;</h2>
<p>Not every directory on this list is right for your business. Submitting to 217 directories would waste time and dilute your effort.</p>
<p>Focus on quality over quantity. Here is how to prioritize.</p>
<h3>Check Domain Authority First</h3>
<p>Directories with higher <a href="/blog/domain-authority-guide/">domain authority</a> pass stronger link equity. Use a tool like Ahrefs or Moz to check the DA of any directory before submitting. Directories with DA 40+ should be your first priority.</p>
<h3>Match Your Exact Industry</h3>
<p>A dentist listing on Zocdoc signals relevance. That same dentist listing on a photography directory does not. Choose directories that match your primary service category exactly.</p>
<h3>Verify the Directory is Active</h3>
<p>Dead directories with no recent updates provide zero value. Check the last update date, recent reviews, and whether the directory still appears in Google results. An inactive directory wastes your submission time.</p>
<h3>Prioritize Directories with Reviews</h3>
<p>Directories that accept customer reviews provide double value. You get a citation plus a review platform. Directories like Avvo, Healthgrades, and G2 carry weight because search engines trust review signals.</p>
